Titolo: Ghajini – The Game

Anno: 2008

Descrizione: Ghajini – The Game is a third-person action game based on the 2008 film Ghajini  It was published in 2008 by FXLabs and Geetha Arts, and distributed by Eros Home Entertainment.  It was hailed as India's first true 3D PC game. The Game consisting of five levels of play, following the story of the protagonist, Sanjay Singhania (portrayed by Aamir Khan), avenging the death of his girlfriend Kalpana by using martial arts, various weapons, and other artefacts.  Ghajini – The Game has earned Rs40 million. and has a manufacturer's suggested retail price (MSRP) of US$14.99The game was designed by Shashi Reddy, who is the chairman of FX Labs, and Ghajini's co-producer Madhu Mantena.



Genere: Action 

Valutazione: N/A
